  "prompt": "Can I get into the CSE in VIT Chennai at 70+ marks?",
  "response": "Admission to the Computer Science and Engineering (CSE) program at VIT Chennai depends on various factors, including your VITEEE (VIT Engineering Entrance Exam) score, your rank, and the cutoff for that particular year.\n\nIf you have scored 70+ marks in VITEEE, you might have a chance, but it's important to consider the following:\n\n1. **Cutoff Trends**: The cutoff for CSE at VIT Chennai can vary each year. In recent years, the cutoff for CSE has been relatively high, often requiring scores in the range of 80-90 or even higher.\n\n2. **Rank**: Your rank in VITEEE is crucial. A score of 70+ might translate to a rank that could be competitive, but you need to check the specific rank cutoffs for the year you are applying.\n\n3. **Other Factors**: VIT also considers factors like the number of applicants, the difficulty of the exam, and the number of available seats.\n\nTo get a clearer picture, I recommend:\n\n- Checking the latest cutoff and rank information on the VIT official website.\n- Contacting VIT admissions office directly for the most accurate and up-to-date information.\n\nWhile a score of 70+ is a good start, you should prepare for other possibilities and consider alternative programs or campuses if your first choice is highly competitive.",
